setHInstColorId(25.10)                                  setHInstColorId(25.10)

Name
       setHInstColorId - Specifies the color ID for a hierarchical instance

Syntax
       setHInstColorId

       [-help]

       <hInstName>

       <colorID>

       [-descendant]

       Specifies the color ID for a hierarchical instance.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each setHInstColorId parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man setHInstColorId

       <hInstName>
              Name  of  the  hierarchical  instance to which this color ID ap-
              plies.

       <colorID>
              Specifies the color ID from 0 to 29. The  color  value  for  the
              color  id  is  the same as specified in the Module Color Prefer-
              ences form (accessed by clicking Floorplan -  Edit  Floorplan  -
              Color Module).

       -descendant
              Specifies  that  the color ID should be applied to the child/de-
              scendant instances as well.

              Default: If no ID is specified, the color id is applied only for
              the top-level instance.

Example
       The following command applies color ID 3 to the  hierarchical  instance
       topModule:

       setHInstColorId topModule 3

